    <title>Computations in intersection rings of flag bundles</title>
    <summary>  Intersection rings of flag varieties and of isotropic flag varieties are
generated by Chern classes of the tautological bundles modulo the relations
coming from multiplicativity of total Chern classes. In this paper we describe
the Groebner bases of the ideals of relations and give applications to
computation of intersections, as implemented in Macaulay2.
</summary>
